SERVICE
========
why service?
when project was running in pod it was not expose directly
to expose you project we have to use service

three types of service:
1.clusterIP->it will expose pod in internal server
2.nodeport-> it will expose pod in external and internal it will provie one ip address(staticip&nodeport)
3.loadbalancer-> it will expose pod externally and internally it will genaerate(staticip&nodeport,DNS) to 

clusterIP
------------
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: myservice-lb
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: frontend
  ports:
    - port: 1111
      targetPort: 80
------------------------------------------------
NodePort
--------
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: myservice-lb
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: frontend
  ports:
    - port: 1111
      targetPort: 80
	  nodePort: between 30000-32767
-------------------------------------------------------
Loadbalancer
------------
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: myservice-lb
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: frontend
  ports:
    - port: 1111
      targetPort: 80
	  nodePort: between 30000-32767
===================================================
Why nodeport between 30000-32767

Ports 1-1024 are reserved for system daemons and well-known services (SSH:22, HTTP:80, HTTPS:443, DNS:53, etc.)

Ports 1024-30000 are often used by applications and system services

Starting at 30000 leaves plenty of room for normal application ports
